  "doc_id": "27104",
  "text": "Even though Deshpande (1996) found no relationship among job satisfaction and ethical climate, [CITATION_1] found that ethical climate associate with pay to satisfaction. Moreover the rules (i.e., codes, policies, reprimands) creating an ethical climate are positively related to job satisfaction as we offered in our hypothesis (H1) and supported by the findings. According to [CITATION_2] , organizational ethics affect job satisfaction, which in turn promotes favorable job attitudes and organizational outcomes. As expected there is a positive association between job satisfaction and charismatic leadership for employee perception of organization as supported in our hypothesis (H2).",
